title: For Sale:  KSG Shotgun 12 gauge "NEW" Black
postcontent: The KSG (Kel-Tec Shotgun) is Kel-Tec CNC’s first entry into the shotgun market. The size, shape, and design is similar to the currently available Kel-Tec RFB rifle, but the KSG ejects downward, instead of forward. The KSG weighs 6.9 lbs. and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1” overall length and an 18.5” cylinder bore barrel. Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 12 rounds of 12 gauge 3” rounds in total (6 per tube). It can also reliably shoot shells as short as 1 3/4" up to the 3". This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard. The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil. The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. The barrel and pump assembly is removed by loosening the 2 front magazine tube nuts with a coin and sliding the assembly forward. This is a special order item and IS NOT STOCKED IN OUR STORE. This item takes 1-3 days to arrive from our local distributor. Check out our website @ www.getgunsnow.com to see pictures of our store or stop in with any questions. Our hours are 9am-5pm Mon –Fri. To celebrate the anniversary, CZUB set their master engraver, Rene Ondra, to the task of creating a special pistol for the occasion. Each pistol is hand-engraved in the Czech Republic in true old-world style, with a hammer pushing the engraver’s tool through each minute detail of the art decorating the slide and frame, which are then polished and finished in a deep, glossy blue. To finish off the look, smooth, high-grade California birds-eye Maple grips are added. Dyed to match the hues of the frame and controls, the grips seem otherworldly, looking less like wood and more like a snapshot sent to Earth from the Hubble Space Telescope. title: For Sale:  VZ2008 W/ MANY ACCESSORIES
postcontent:
I am selling my VZ2008 w/ folding stock and accessories that includes the following: 

- 5  Magazines ( 30rd. 7.62x39mm ) 
- Bayonet and Sheath ( Bayonet has been sharpened and pointed )
- Leather Sling 
- Leather Magazine Pouch  
- Cleaning Kit 
- I created a very simple and comfortable cheek guard for the wire stock ( purchased copper tube styrofoam insulation from home depot and cut to size, works very nicely ) 


Some information about this rifle: 

- The VZ2008 is a surplus parts kit that has been assembled by Century Arms and sold online and in store by many retailers 

- Although the VZ2008 looks very similar to an AK47, the only thing it shares in common is the caliber it fires, the 7.62x39mm ( Magazines are NOT interchangeable with AK47 ) 

- This gun is a Czechoslovakian design from the 1950's that is still in used to this day by the Czech republic as well as Slovakia ( http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vz._58 ) 


Technical Information about rifle: 

- It is a milled receiver that is lighter and more accurate than the AK47 

- Folding wire stock makes this rifle very compact and convenient for storage and transportation 

- The gun has a bolt open feature on the last round  

- The handguard is made of a wood/polymer mixture and as such, after a few magazines tends to get hot. This can be easily modified by replacing the wood, or adjusting your grip closer to the magazine


Feedback: 

-There are many reviews of this rifle, the VZ2008 online, and I can try and provide you with a number of different sources to read through, but a simple search on youtube for VZ2008 or a google search will bring up everyone's experience

- I can tell you that the rifle I have has been 100% reliable when I have been shooting it, and while I haven't put thousands of rounds through it, I have put over 150 rounds and not experienced one problem

- First video when searching VZ2008 on youtube: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kXtO7KLip9M

- First website review when seraching VZ2008: http://www.thefirearmblog.com/blog/2013/10/04/vz2008-vs-700-rounds/




Information about this specific rifle: 

- I have taken this gun out to the range and fired 150 rounds through it to test functionality of magazines and firearm ( 30rds x 5 magazines ) It was 100% reliable, with very powerful spent casing ejecting many feet away from shooter

- I was able to hit pop cans at 35-45 yards one first/second shot with this rifle, sights are dead on 

- Much lighter than any AK47 I have ever shot, and surprisingly accurate and ate all 150 rds. fired through it with no issues ( I used Tula purchased from Walmart for the test ) 

- Folding stock took a little while of practice to get right, but now I am able to open and close it with no effort ( The stock opens and closes the same when the cheek guard is on as well )



**IMPORTANT** Starting after January 1st, 2013, Michigan Law regarding folding stocks on long guns has changed. This weapon was purchased after Jan 1st, 2013 and thus falls under the new legal terms for a long rifle. It meets the criteria set in the law which is the following: 

- The rifle is AT LEAST 26" in over all length WITH the stock folded or contracted And the barrel is AT LEAST 16" in length


(^What the above means is that this firearm is considered the same as any other Long gun, and what what means is it can be sold/purchased via private buyer in similar fashion, thus why this is being posted here instead of the Handgun forum)


Reason why I am selling: 

I am trying to get back what I put into this rifle when I purchased it so I can convert the cash into another AR15 purchase. I am looking for serious buyers who are willing to meet me, or be very close to the price I am asking, and as such, I would request that only serious offers within the ballpark of my request contact me. I am willing to drive within an hour of Farmington Hills to try and help the sale/purchase of this firearm. 

pictures can be found at the following link: http://imgur.com/a/8v0KA#0

title: For Sale:  SPYDERCO MILITARY CAMO ~ C36GCMO
postcontent:
length overall	9.5" (241 mm)	blade length	4" (102 mm)	blade steel	CPM S30V
length closed	5.5" (140 mm)	cutting edge	3.687" (94 mm)	weight	4.25 oz (120 g)
blade thickness	.145" (3.7 mm)	handle material	G-10
Digital Camouflage is the outcome of applying engineering psychology with the study of visual biophysics and human visual performance.The pattern is made up of small micropatterns, optically reducing the eye's ability to detect and discern what it covers.Various digital patterns are developed and used for the U.S. Military to make more effective concealment for the men and women who go in harms way to protect our freedom.

A cornerstone model in Spyderco's Save and Serve line up is the C36 Military Model meeting the requirements of a high-performance, light-weight folder designed for hard use. Since the steel is the spirit of the knife, CPM S30V seemed the logical choice for the blade given its reputation for long-term edge retention and rust resistance. The 'Millie' has a modified clip-point blade laser cut with a 14 mm Spyderco Round Hole for quick deployment and for use with gloves. Texturing above the hole hold the thumb in contact with the blade's spine during cutting for confident control over the sharpened edge. The handle scales are Digital Camouflage G-10 with the lock's liner nested (inlayed) directly into the scale, pumping up lock strength without the addition of bulky liners. Spacers between the scales create a gap running the handle's full length exposing the inside workings for inspection and cleaning. The handle flares slightly at the front end creating a finger choil and at the butt end, which keeps the knife from slipping forward or backward in the hand while sawing or making tough or aggressive cuts. A contoured black metal clip is set for right-hand tip-down carry.

title: For Sale:  Black Ops Tactical Sniper Pellet Rifle Professional Grade w/ Upgraded Crosman Scope
postcontent:
I bought this air rifle a month ago for $150 from Wal-Mart of all places after spending months studying different types of air rifles, brands, mechanisms, reading reviews, etc. When I bought it, it was only available on the Wal-Mart website. Now it is listed as sold out and I can't find any at local stores. However, I noticed Amazon is now selling this air rifle for about $150 + shipping. 

I was surprised by the overwhelmingly positive reviews that I read on Wal-Mart's website and was suspicious at first, considering I had never heard of the company this air rifle is sold by, "Ignite" or "Black Ops." It had a perfect 5 star rating with over 30 reviews and having just recently been introduced on Amazon currently has a perfect 5 star rating there as well. 

I was willing to spend over $200, but this rifle is better BY FAR in all categories than well known air rifles from commonly known brands in the same price range. It is a spring piston, break barrel, 1000 FPS, 0.177 cal, fully adjustable stock and bipod. It comes with a 4x32 scope that is very accurate, surprisingly so for a stock scope that probably isn't worth more than $20. 

Nonetheless, I felt the caliber (as in excellence) of the weapon warranted an upgrade. So, a week later I bought a new Crosman 3-9x32mm scope with a zoom dial allowing 3x to 9x magnification, making it perfect for hunting and long distance target practice. This scope comes with a red/green dual illumination mil-dot reticle that has the option of 5 brightness settings for both green or red. Holds zero extremely well, and is tough enough to withstand the recoil for a break barrel rifle like this but is also commonly used as a scope for .22 rifles. This air rifle is easily accurate from 100 yards+ and the upgraded scope makes that number closer to 200 yards or more. While it is listed as 1000 FPS (using quality 0.177 pellets as heavy as JSB Match Exact Diabolo airgun pellets weighing in at 8.44gr or slightly lighter pellets such as Crosman Premier Hollow Point hunting pellets) I have read reports that is more in the range of 1000-1200 FPS. If you're using non-lead pellets that usually weigh about 4gr give or take you can expect even higher FPS. I've killed multiple squirrels using this weapon, and it's so accurate and powerful I've never missed or had to finish one off. The only reason I am selling it is I am behind on court ordered restitution payments and need the money, so I'm basically selling just about anything of value I own. Will ship anywhere in the US, though it would certainly be easier if someone local wanted to buy it. If you live in the OKC area give or take 30-50 miles I am willing to drive to you for the sale. 

As I mentioned this is essentially a brand new air rifle, comes with instruction manual, upgraded scope (and stock scope if you want it as well), allen wrenches for adjustments, and I'll even throw in all my pellets including Predator Polymag pellets with sharp pointed polymer tips for maximum penetration (value $18/200 ct), Crosman Hollow Point hunting pellets (value $8/500 ct), JSB Diabolo Exact pellets (value $13/500 ct), and some Gamo Rocket Ballistic Tip pellets (value $5/150 ct) if you want them for no extra charge (all tins have AT LEAST half the pellets remaining, though 75% is more accurate. Bottom line, plenty of pellets to find the perfect match for you). 

As for the price, considering it is basically brand new with original box, manual, less than 100 pellets shot and based on the only other two I have seen sold online I value the stock air rifle (without upgraded scope) at $125 and considering the value of the upgraded scope which is listed at over $70 (but was purchased by me for slightly less), I'd value the entire package (rifle, upgraded scope, all original packaging) at the base price of $150. That said, I need to get rid of it within a couple months so the price is $120 + shipping (if not a local sale).

If you have questions, would like to see pictures, or are interested in purchase, please either e-mail me at REDACTED or text me at (405) eight-one-eight five-eight two-nine. You may also call, but I don't answer numbers I don't know so leave a message and I will return your call within 24 hours.
